    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-02-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-02-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="398"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d398">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">884A.00/2–852</note>
                <head>No. 398<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d398fn1">Addressed also to Director for Mutual Security
                            <persName corresp="#p_HWA1">Harriman</persName> and Director of the
                        Bureau of the Budget <persName corresp="#p_LFJ1">Lawton</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-02-08">February 8,
                            1952</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I understand that the tentative budget figures for Mutual Security for fiscal
                    year 1953 include the sum $25 million for Israel. I further understand that a
                    program for Israel aggregating about $80 million has been developed within the
                    Department of State. After considering the various aspects of the situation, I
                    believe that the program for Israel for fiscal year 1953 should total $80
                    million, and that the additonal $55 million should be in addition to the amounts
                    heretofore contemplated for economic aid.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_THS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harry Truman</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
